00:00:08,750 --> 00:00:13,367
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

3
00:00:13,367 --> 00:00:15,689
Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:18,290
I’ve never seen Grandma so excited.

5
00:00:18,290 --> 00:00:20,458
She must be thrilled to be back here.

6
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:22,208
I want a good father for my children.

7
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:23,610
I want a good husband.

8
00:00:23,610 --> 00:00:25,010
And if you can’t give me that,

9
00:00:25,010 --> 00:00:26,943
then we’re better off divorced.

10
00:00:26,943 --> 00:00:29,819
I won’t be able to
help you with Grandma anymore.

11
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:30,985
It’s all good, Rak.

12
00:00:30,985 --> 00:00:33,700
You need to take care of your family now.

13
00:00:33,896 --> 00:00:36,936
Our love won’t end because of this.

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,755
FOUR MONTHS LATER

15
00:00:48,258 --> 00:00:58,198
TIME TO WAKE UP… MY LOVE

16
00:01:13,346 --> 00:01:13,929
Rak.

17
00:02:42,228 --> 00:02:44,124
(Dear My Pretty Lady,)

18
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,815
(Do you still like to
wear that cold, grumpy face?)

19
00:02:48,559 --> 00:02:52,195
(Learn to smile
and find joy in the little things.)

20
00:02:52,847 --> 00:02:56,927
(If that’s too hard,
here are some small tricks from me.)

21
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,252
(First, go jogging in the morning.)

22
00:03:01,635 --> 00:03:04,934
(It'll refresh your body and keep you healthy.)

23
00:03:05,432 --> 00:03:06,637
(And…

24
00:03:07,078 --> 00:03:09,824
imagine me running beside you every morning.)

25
00:03:23,547 --> 00:03:27,900
(Second, water the plants and feed the fish.)

26
00:03:28,571 --> 00:03:30,592
(Don’t forget to give them your smile too.)

27
00:03:32,259 --> 00:03:34,272
(I’ll be watching from here to see if you do.)

28
00:03:39,121 --> 00:03:42,927
(Lastly, dinner is family time.)

29
00:03:43,981 --> 00:03:45,093
(Don’t forget to eat.)

30
00:03:45,936 --> 00:03:47,233
(Never skip a meal.)

31
00:03:47,942 --> 00:03:49,072
(I care so much about you.)

32
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,557
Is the soup good?

33
00:03:50,557 --> 00:03:51,126
Very good.

34
00:03:51,854 --> 00:03:52,557
It’s nice and hot.

35
00:03:54,704 --> 00:03:55,317
Yum!

36
00:03:55,317 --> 00:03:56,051
There you go.

37
00:03:56,492 --> 00:03:57,402
Good, huh?

38
00:03:57,881 --> 00:03:59,662
I told you it’s good.

39
00:04:31,182 --> 00:04:32,574
(Dear My Love,)

40
00:04:33,283 --> 00:04:35,328
(I do everything you told me to.)

41
00:04:36,574 --> 00:04:38,228
(I feel happy every day.)

42
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:40,593
(I smile every day.)

43
00:04:42,471 --> 00:04:44,691
(But somehow, when the night comes,

44
00:04:45,553 --> 00:04:47,336
the loneliness always creeps in.)

45
00:04:48,831 --> 00:04:50,910
(Maybe it’s because I miss you.)

46
00:04:51,772 --> 00:04:53,832
(All I can do is hope
that when morning comes,

47
00:04:54,139 --> 00:04:56,033
I can smile again,

48
00:04:56,416 --> 00:04:58,570
just like the way you always smiled at me.)

49
00:06:16,935 --> 00:06:21,273
SAY FAREWELL AND START FRESH

50
00:06:23,688 --> 00:06:24,200
Rak.

51
00:06:25,982 --> 00:06:26,680
Yes, Mom?

52
00:06:27,082 --> 00:06:28,262
Are you reading?

53
00:06:30,082 --> 00:06:30,620
Yes.

54
00:06:32,862 --> 00:06:37,418
I can’t believe
kids these days still write postcards.

55
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:43,144
Pam and I just think it’s a classic.

56
00:06:43,757 --> 00:06:45,414
It holds sentimental value,

57
00:06:46,909 --> 00:06:48,080
and we can take it out to read anytime.

58
00:06:52,028 --> 00:06:54,660
So, how’s Kawi doing today?

59
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,108
He’s okay.

60
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,184
He talked to me just fine

61
00:07:00,836 --> 00:07:02,330
and came out of his room for every meal.

62
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,467
Thanks, Rak,

63
00:07:06,984 --> 00:07:08,292
for helping me take care of your brother.

64
00:07:10,151 --> 00:07:11,532
It’s my pleasure.

65
00:07:13,717 --> 00:07:14,915
I’m his sister.

66
00:07:19,821 --> 00:07:21,870
I want him to recover quickly.

67
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:32,705
I’m sure he will get better.

68
00:07:41,113 --> 00:07:45,333
When do you think
he’ll be able to return to work?

69
00:07:48,246 --> 00:07:50,608
From my perspective,

70
00:07:52,122 --> 00:07:53,852
I’d prefer for him to rest well

71
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,119
and fully recover first.

72
00:07:56,579 --> 00:07:59,367
I don’t want anything heavy to affect him.

73
00:08:00,536 --> 00:08:04,901
But ultimately, it’s his decision.

74
00:08:58,830 --> 00:08:59,564
Why are you here?

75
00:09:00,369 --> 00:09:02,234
We brought you some snacks, Nene.

76
00:09:06,297 --> 00:09:06,806
I’m not hungry.

77
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:12,977
Have you eaten?

78
00:09:15,391 --> 00:09:15,944
No,

79
00:09:16,653 --> 00:09:17,443
but I’m not hungry.

80
00:09:22,656 --> 00:09:23,849
Are you sure?

81
00:09:24,194 --> 00:09:25,600
We have coconut pudding,

82
00:09:25,696 --> 00:09:26,791
fried dough sticks,

83
00:09:27,021 --> 00:09:27,942
and grilled pork skewers.

84
00:09:28,325 --> 00:09:29,500
All good stuff.

85
00:09:36,783 --> 00:09:39,420
Look, just be honest with me.

86
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,120
Why are you really here?

87
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:45,173
I know you didn’t come just to bring me food.

88
00:09:52,111 --> 00:09:59,314
Actually, I wanted to ask if
you’d come with me to visit Kawi at home.

89
00:10:07,049 --> 00:10:08,561
I don’t want to set foot in that house.

90
00:10:12,643 --> 00:10:16,682
Just thinking about how your father
used to live there makes me sick.

91
00:10:18,369 --> 00:10:20,129
Dad hasn’t lived there for a long time now.

92
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:25,598
Even if I go, it won’t make anything better.

93
00:10:27,342 --> 00:10:28,801
We’re not even related.

94
00:10:34,359 --> 00:10:35,975
Well, if we think about it,

95
00:10:36,435 --> 00:10:41,043
you share the same blood as Kawi and Dokrak.

96
00:10:42,135 --> 00:10:44,916
So, technically, you guys are related.

97
00:10:46,162 --> 00:10:46,830
That’s right.

98
00:10:47,884 --> 00:10:49,885
Nene, you’re Kawi’s little sister

99
00:10:51,054 --> 00:10:52,180
and my big sister.

100
00:10:56,205 --> 00:10:57,712
We’re siblings.

101
00:10:59,878 --> 00:11:01,182
You’re not alone.

102
00:11:02,332 --> 00:11:03,636
You have a family.

103
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,652
You have special guests today.

104
00:11:36,725 --> 00:11:37,963
Hello, Kawi.

105
00:11:38,557 --> 00:11:39,163
Oat.

106
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:17,338
You have special guests today.

107
00:12:25,576 --> 00:12:26,763
Hello, Kawi.

108
00:12:30,497 --> 00:12:31,099
Oat.

109
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:47,284
Kawi.

110
00:12:51,124 --> 00:12:52,074
How are you doing?

111
00:12:54,613 --> 00:12:55,194
I…

112
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:02,451
I’m recovering.

113
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:04,540
What about you, Nene?

114
00:13:05,372 --> 00:13:06,651
Are you fully healed?

115
00:13:11,856 --> 00:13:13,276
If you mean physically,

116
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:15,742
then yes.

117
00:13:22,142 --> 00:13:23,174
Same here.

118
00:13:29,015 --> 00:13:31,102
Since you both still need healing,

119
00:13:34,430 --> 00:13:36,214
why not heal each other?

120
00:13:39,798 --> 00:13:40,958
What are you doing?

121
00:13:41,747 --> 00:13:43,955
I just want you and Kawi to fully recover.

122
00:13:45,982 --> 00:13:47,260
And what am I supposed to do?

123
00:13:48,455 --> 00:13:54,887
Well, what would you do
if your family member was feeling down?

124
00:14:23,122 --> 00:14:25,055
Can I get a hug from my big brother…

125
00:14:27,466 --> 00:14:29,274
and sister, please?

126
00:15:48,302 --> 00:15:51,372
Rak, slow down, will you?

127
00:15:51,457 --> 00:15:52,559
This is so good.

128
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:54,453
You’re an amazing cook.

129
00:15:54,532 --> 00:15:55,310
I didn’t know this before.

130
00:15:57,870 --> 00:16:00,540
I just realized you’re a good cook too.

131
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:07,195
Then I’ll cook for you guys again sometime.

132
00:16:15,172 --> 00:16:15,828
Here.

133
00:16:17,215 --> 00:16:17,886
Eat more.

134
00:16:19,273 --> 00:16:20,054
Have the pork too.

135
00:16:28,987 --> 00:16:29,965
Mom, are you okay?

136
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:34,878
I’m just thinking about your father.

137
00:16:36,073 --> 00:16:40,101
I think it’s time we clear things up.

138
00:16:41,509 --> 00:16:42,368
That’s a good idea.

139
00:16:43,755 --> 00:16:44,680
We can finally settle everything.

140
00:16:45,298 --> 00:16:49,226
But I don’t think he’ll give in so easily.

141
00:16:55,865 --> 00:16:56,476
Mom,

142
00:16:59,506 --> 00:17:00,980
don’t worry.

143
00:17:03,135 --> 00:17:04,750
You’re not in this alone.

144
00:17:07,331 --> 00:17:08,431
You still have me

145
00:17:09,818 --> 00:17:11,009
and Dokrak with you.

146
00:17:15,276 --> 00:17:16,231
Kawi,

147
00:17:17,746 --> 00:17:19,744
you don’t have to face him, sweetheart.

148
00:17:22,496 --> 00:17:24,322
I’ll handle everything.

149
00:17:25,282 --> 00:17:26,714
You don’t need to do anything.

150
00:17:31,365 --> 00:17:33,226
Even though I’m not fully recovered,

151
00:17:35,253 --> 00:17:36,737
I want to stand by you.

152
00:17:38,145 --> 00:17:39,106
Please let me.

153
00:17:44,802 --> 00:17:46,070
I’ll stand by you too.

154
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:53,231
Thanks.

155
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:56,406
Now let’s eat.

156
00:18:12,249 --> 00:18:13,112
So good.

157
00:18:14,242 --> 00:18:14,954
Have a bite.

158
00:18:20,287 --> 00:18:22,162
You took all the skin.

159
00:18:22,772 --> 00:18:24,215
I won’t share it next time.

160
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:28,711
Your generosity is short-lived.

161
00:18:29,266 --> 00:18:31,182
It’s the best part!

162
00:18:31,502 --> 00:18:32,488
Have another piece then.

163
00:18:33,469 --> 00:18:34,526
I’m just kidding.

164
00:18:36,318 --> 00:18:37,797
Mom, you should eat too.

165
00:18:38,309 --> 00:18:39,018
Thank you.

166
00:18:42,602 --> 00:18:45,110
I did everything you asked, Orn.

167
00:18:46,049 --> 00:18:48,085
I also gave up the house for you and the kids.

168
00:18:49,109 --> 00:18:50,447
Isn’t that enough?

169
00:18:52,303 --> 00:18:53,553
But I don’t want it.

170
00:18:55,366 --> 00:18:57,305
What I want is for us to divorce.

171
00:19:00,078 --> 00:19:01,232
Sign the papers, Khem,

172
00:19:02,597 --> 00:19:04,085
before things get more complicated.

173
00:19:08,053 --> 00:19:11,002
Orn, we can’t get divorced.

174
00:19:11,749 --> 00:19:12,901
Think about it.

175
00:19:13,328 --> 00:19:14,635
Will your family accept this?

176
00:19:15,062 --> 00:19:18,663
My family definitely won’t be okay with this.

177
00:19:19,431 --> 00:19:20,720
And you're involving the law now.

178
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:24,272
Why do you have to escalate things, Orn?

179
00:19:24,272 --> 00:19:27,053
All we need to do is get back to being a family.

180
00:19:28,184 --> 00:19:30,319
Is this what you call family?

181
00:19:30,511 --> 00:19:33,199
The word "family" died a long time ago for us.

182
00:19:33,946 --> 00:19:35,936
There’s no love, no care left.

183
00:19:36,448 --> 00:19:38,228
Only your selfishness remains.

184
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:39,520
Orn!

185
00:19:39,925 --> 00:19:41,703
How could you speak to me like that?

186
00:19:42,834 --> 00:19:44,392
Mom has every right to say that.

187
00:19:45,032 --> 00:19:46,212
For all this time,

188
00:19:46,788 --> 00:19:50,483
you’ve known exactly how you’ve hurt her.

189
00:19:53,406 --> 00:19:55,138
For the sake of what we used to be,

190
00:19:58,381 --> 00:19:59,695
just let Mom and us go.

191
00:20:00,719 --> 00:20:01,744
Sign the divorce papers.

192
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,509
Shut your mouth!

193
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:04,831
This is adult business.

194
00:20:05,066 --> 00:20:06,215
It’s my business too.

195
00:20:07,175 --> 00:20:09,452
This is my mom and my brother.

196
00:20:10,497 --> 00:20:12,166
I’m not letting you do this anymore.

197
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:13,384
Rak, you—!

198
00:20:13,725 --> 00:20:14,634
Please stop, Dad.

199
00:20:16,652 --> 00:20:18,120
Everything’s over now.

200
00:20:20,061 --> 00:20:21,883
No one wants to stay with you anymore.

201
00:20:22,907 --> 00:20:24,280
Kawi, how dare you…

202
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,581
Fine.

203
00:20:33,202 --> 00:20:34,318
You want a divorce?

204
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:36,314
Go ahead and sue for a divorce.

205
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:39,250
But you’re not getting any of my assets.

206
00:20:41,298 --> 00:20:43,529
I’m not letting you guys keep my last name.

207
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:45,666
I’m kicking you all out of the house.

208
00:20:46,391 --> 00:20:47,955
Take nothing with you when you leave!

209
00:20:49,619 --> 00:20:50,172
Fine.

210
00:20:53,351 --> 00:20:54,692
My children and I will go.

211
00:20:55,481 --> 00:20:56,224
Go.

212
00:20:57,077 --> 00:21:01,521
I’d love to see how you’ll survive without me.

213
00:21:02,673 --> 00:21:03,905
Of course, we’ll survive.

214
00:21:07,893 --> 00:21:10,829
We may not have a house, but we have family.

215
00:21:11,405 --> 00:21:12,856
We’ll make it through.

216
00:21:13,581 --> 00:21:15,229
All we need is each other.

217
00:21:16,445 --> 00:21:17,784
You’re the one who should think hard.

218
00:21:18,595 --> 00:21:20,358
Without "family,"

219
00:21:21,339 --> 00:21:22,516
how are you going to live?

220
00:21:26,015 --> 00:21:27,243
I’ll live just fine.

221
00:21:29,014 --> 00:21:31,745
You’re the ones who’ll struggle.

222
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:34,622
Is that so?

223
00:21:34,963 --> 00:21:36,104
We’ll see about that.

224
00:21:40,968 --> 00:21:41,588
Let’s go.

225
00:21:43,039 --> 00:21:43,694
Come with me.

226
00:21:47,278 --> 00:21:48,856
Leave and don’t ever come back.

227
00:21:49,112 --> 00:21:52,300
I can’t wait to see how you’ll survive
without me backing you up.

228
00:22:20,273 --> 00:22:20,844
Hello.

229
00:22:22,652 --> 00:22:23,713
Do you have time tonight, baby?

230
00:22:25,142 --> 00:22:26,429
I’m feeling lonely here.

231
00:22:26,578 --> 00:22:27,510
Come see me.

232
00:22:29,537 --> 00:22:30,182
Mm.

233
00:22:30,481 --> 00:22:31,640
I’ll have someone pick you up.

234
00:22:38,936 --> 00:22:39,796
Maid.

235
00:22:41,396 --> 00:22:42,290
Maid!

236
00:22:43,805 --> 00:22:45,164
Is anyone here?

237
00:22:51,009 --> 00:22:52,528
Prepare dinner for two.

238
00:22:53,339 --> 00:22:54,133
I’m having a guest over.

239
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:54,634
Yes, sir.

240
00:22:54,741 --> 00:22:55,830
(Pam,

241
00:22:57,430 --> 00:22:59,514
Dad finally agreed to divorce Mom.)

242
00:23:00,218 --> 00:23:01,863
(While we search for a new house,

243
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:05,391
Nene has let us stay at hers.)

244
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,419
(As for the old house,

245
00:23:08,718 --> 00:23:12,472
Dad’s living there alone now.)

246
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:23,055
The santol and rambai trees are in bloom.

247
00:23:23,226 --> 00:23:24,338
Look at your mango tree.

248
00:23:25,191 --> 00:23:28,652
Oh, the mango tree is in full bloom now.

249
00:23:28,652 --> 00:23:29,602
They already look delicious.

250
00:23:30,071 --> 00:23:32,113
I think we’ll get lots of fruit this season.

251
00:23:32,241 --> 00:23:32,793
True.

252
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:38,715
Why are you in such a good mood today?

253
00:23:46,694 --> 00:23:47,348
Grandma.

254
00:23:47,348 --> 00:23:48,334
Hm?

255
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:49,987
I think…

256
00:23:50,371 --> 00:23:53,315
Dokrak will be coming to see us soon.

257
00:23:54,104 --> 00:23:55,646
That’s good.

258
00:23:56,926 --> 00:23:59,550
I miss her.

259
00:24:01,001 --> 00:24:03,339
All we can do is chat over video calls.

260
00:24:04,427 --> 00:24:06,480
I can’t wait to see her in person.

261
00:24:07,248 --> 00:24:09,512
You miss your chess buddy, don’t you?

262
00:24:09,768 --> 00:24:10,902
I do.

263
00:24:11,521 --> 00:24:14,037
Playing with Rak is so much fun,

264
00:24:14,677 --> 00:24:17,473
unlike Titang, who always loses.

265
00:24:17,473 --> 00:24:20,730
Come on, I pretend not to be good for you.

266
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,342
You’re actually not good.

267
00:24:22,427 --> 00:24:23,061
Wow.

268
00:24:23,232 --> 00:24:25,013
You’re starting to diss like a teenager now.

269
00:24:25,525 --> 00:24:29,525
Dokrak taught me
when we were video calling.

270
00:24:30,378 --> 00:24:32,469
What else does she teach you?

271
00:24:32,810 --> 00:24:33,853
Wait until I see her.

272
00:24:33,938 --> 00:24:35,068
I’m going to pinch her cheek!

273
00:24:46,351 --> 00:24:46,956
Grandma.

274
00:24:46,956 --> 00:24:47,773
Hm?

275
00:24:48,221 --> 00:24:49,679
Once Dokrak is here,

276
00:24:50,298 --> 00:24:52,276
how about we take her out to see the sunset?

277
00:24:52,895 --> 00:24:53,880
Sounds good.

278
00:24:54,755 --> 00:24:58,648
The weather’s nice,
and everything’s getting better.

279
00:24:59,971 --> 00:25:02,979
Thanks a lot, Pam,

280
00:25:03,107 --> 00:25:05,194
for bringing me to live here.

281
00:25:07,306 --> 00:25:09,130
You should thank Dokrak.

282
00:25:09,685 --> 00:25:11,476
It was her idea.

283
00:25:12,415 --> 00:25:15,901
Say thanks to her for me then.

284
00:25:16,652 --> 00:25:18,317
Why should I do it?

285
00:25:18,765 --> 00:25:20,495
You can just tell her when you see her.

286
00:25:20,836 --> 00:25:22,697
Yeah, you’re right.

287
00:25:25,534 --> 00:25:28,123
I’m old and forgetful.

288
00:25:34,182 --> 00:25:36,895
Goodness, the weather today is really nice.

289
00:26:09,716 --> 00:26:10,869
Hello, Pam.

290
